                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.01/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-19T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 19, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Your 224, May 15, 2 p.m. You may answer Peruvian Government’s note of March
                        12<note n="25" xml:id="d1008fn25">See telegram No. 116, March 13, noon, from
                        the Ambassador in Peru, <ref target="#pg_912">p. 912</ref>.</note> last and
                    state that the change in government in Peru will make no difference in the
                    diplomatic relations between the United States and Peru.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
